lead_paragraph: An article on Sunday about the strong effort by Tyson Gay in the 200-meter race at the Reebok Grand Prix track meet on Randalls Island referred incorrectly to his performance in the 100 meters at the Beijing Olympics. He was fifth in a semifinal heat and failed to qualify for the finals; he did not finish “a distant fifth” behind Usain Bolt of Jamaica in the finals.
